metadata.name: Because The Internet - Script
metadata.description: Because the internet, we are able to tell this story. We can explore the themes of connectivity and its challenges, and examine how the digital world has impacted our lives. Through the use of technology, we can bring this story to life and engage with audiences in a way that was not possible before the internet. Because of the internet, we have the opportunity to share this tale and connect with others in a meaningful way.   Because The Internet is a 2013 studio album by Donald Glover, also known by his stage name Childish Gambino. The album, which was released on December 6, 2013, explores themes of connectivity, technology, and the impact of the internet on modern society. The album features a mix of genres, including hip hop, pop, and electronic music, and was a critical and commercial success. It was nominated for Best Rap Album at the 56th Grammy Awards, and spawned several successful singles, including "3005" and "Sober".  This is the script to goes along to the album.
